Hello! Have we met? More than likely yes! My Name is Katie Wilson, and I’m her personal assistant, front of house staff, and apprentice. I’ve been with Caitlin since 2021, and what an amazing journey it’s been so far! I handle her social media page, scheduling, photo editing, phone calls, etc. I do a lot of the behind the scenes work! Working for one of the absolute best piercing studios in Toledo has given me so much pride, self validation in my abilities, and has really given me a chance to improve my skills! Caitlin has trusted my ideas and opinions, given me advice on where to improve and how to succeed, given me the tools I need to further my career and education, all while providing a great and fun work environment! I cannot wait to grow with her as a person, friend, and employee! Forever thankful for this lifestyle she has provided me. This year I’m attending @safepiercing APP conference with her, and taking multiple courses to enhance my professional outlook on things, employee and clientele communications and developments, how to handle certain situations, styling advice, diversity and inclusion courses, and as well as piercing studies as I’m about to start engaging more on my apprenticeship! It’s been so much fun starting this journey with you all, and I cannot wait to assist you on future endeavors. 🌸💕✨ Thank you #Toledo !  Picture: What is your fav coffee?: Shaken turtle iced latte from @brewhousemaumee ! What do you love best about your job?:Having my ideas supported, learning and obtaining as much knowledge as I can, and being able to create a easy flowing environment for clients and piercers! Being relied on means so much to me! I’m your “go-to” person!! What is your biggest achievement so far?: Becoming a new mother and being able to show her you can have a successful fulfilling work life. I’m extremely  proud of myself and the work that I’ve done. Advancing my career, learning new abilities, creating new ways to expand our business, perfecting our way of life to make things easier, I succeed well with multiple challenges and projects. Becoming a person she can look up too and be proud of as well is definitely my biggest accomplishment!

When it comes to choosing body jewelry, one of the most crucial decisions you'll make is the type of material it's made of. While there are various options available, solid 14kt gold stands out as a superior choice compared to plated gold. Here’s why~
Genuine Beauty: Solid 14kt gold possesses a natural and captivating luster that simply cannot be replicated by plated gold. Unlike plated jewelry, which is typically made of a base metal coated with a thin layer of gold, solid gold body jewelry is made entirely of genuine gold throughout. This results in a rich and vibrant appearance that will remain consistent over time, without the risk of the underlying metal showing through.
Allergen-Free: Allergies are a significant concern when it comes to body jewelry. Many people experience adverse reactions to metals such as nickel or brass, which are commonly used as base metals in plated jewelry. Solid 14kt gold, on the other hand, is hypoallergenic, making it an excellent choice for those with sensitive skin. It significantly reduces the risk of irritation or allergic reactions, ensuring a comfortable and enjoyable wearing experience.
Durability and Longevity: One of the most significant advantages of solid gold jewelry is its exceptional durability. Gold is a precious metal that is naturally resistant to tarnish, corrosion, and rust. Unlike plated jewelry, which may wear off or peel over time, solid 14kt gold maintains its integrity and appearance for generations. With proper care, your solid gold body jewelry can last a lifetime, making it a valuable investment.
While plated gold body jewelry may be more affordable initially, it falls short when it comes to the timeless elegance, durability, hypoallergenic properties, and value that solid 14kt gold provides. Investing in solid gold not only allows you to enjoy its inherent beauty but also ensures that you have a lasting and reliable piece of jewelry that will be cherished for years to come.

It's important to address an alarming issue in some piercing studios: The practice of offering different prices for genital piercings based on the anatomy involved. (Ex. One form of genital piercing is higher priced than the opposite sex) Let's shed light on why this is not only unfair but also perpetuates harmful stereotypes and discrimination:

Such practices contribute to inequality and prejudice within the community. Every individual deserves equal treatment and respect, regardless of their gender. Studios that offer different prices for genital piercings based on anatomy contribute to an environment that disregards equality and inclusivity. It's crucial to create safe spaces where everyone feels welcomed and valued.

2.Expertise Should Determine Pricing: Pricing should be based on the expertise and skill required to perform a specific piercing, rather than the gender or anatomy involved. Each piercing, regardless of its location, demands careful technique, knowledge of anatomy, and adherence to strict safety protocols. It's the professionalism and proficiency of the piercer that should determine the price, not societal biases. A shop that prefers ‘female’ based anatomy and offering cheaper piercings for that region compared to ‘male’ based anatomy is a HUGE red flag. All base genital piercings should start at the same price. 

3.Body modification, including genital piercings, should be celebrated as an expression of personal choice and individuality. By treating all genital piercings with equal respect and pricing, studios can help foster a positive body image for individuals of all genders. Everyone should feel empowered and supported in their journey towards self-expression.
As a consumer, it's essential to advocate for equality and fairness within the piercing community. Choose studios that embrace inclusivity, value all types of genital piercings equally, and prioritize the well-being and satisfaction of their clients.

When choosing a piercing shop, it’s essential to keep an eye out for red flags that could indicate potential issues with safety, hygiene, or the professionalism of the establishment. Here are some piercing shop red flags to watch out for:
Poor hygiene practices: If the shop appears dirty, cluttered, or lacks proper cleaning protocols, it’s a major red flag. A clean and well-maintained environment is crucial for preventing infections and ensuring your safety.
Unqualified or inexperienced piercers: Ensure that the piercers at the shop are experienced, knowledgeable, and certified (some states do not require certification, like Ohio) If they cannot provide credentials or seem unsure about proper techniques and safety measures, it’s best to find a different shop.
Limited or poor-quality jewelry selection: A reputable piercing shop should offer a variety of high-quality jewelry options. If the selection is limited, and the jewelry appears cheap or of low quality, it could be a sign that the shop doesn’t prioritize your long-term well-being.
Lack of aftercare guidance: Adequate aftercare is crucial for the healing process. If the shop doesn’t provide clear aftercare instructions or fails to explain how to care for your piercing properly, it’s a warning sign. 
Poor communication and customer service: If the staff is rude, dismissive, or unwilling to answer your questions and address your concerns, it’s a red flag. Good communication and customer service are essential in any professional establishment.

Say No to Harmful Materials! 🚫✨ Let’s dive into the significance of caring for your piercing correctly and why it’s crucial to avoid harmful substances.

Saline Solution: Use a sterile saline solution specifically formulated for wound care to clean your piercing. Saline helps flush out bacteria, reduces inflammation, and promotes healing without causing irritation. Neilmed is an excellent saline solution to use! 
Drying: After cleansing your piercing, it’s essential to thoroughly dry the area. Moisture can create a breeding ground for bacteria, potentially leading to infections or other complications. Gently patting the piercing dry with a clean, disposable paper towel or using a hairdryer to help dry the area. 
No Swimming: During the initial healing phase, it’s highly recommended to avoid swimming, especially in bodies of water such as pools, lakes, rivers, and hot tubs. A minimum of 4-8 weeks!!!
Avoid Harsh Products and Irritants: Steer clear of harsh chemicals, alcohol-based solutions, hydrogen peroxide, and other irritants. These can disrupt the natural healing process, dry out the skin, and cause further irritation.
🚫 Tea Tree Oil: Despite its touted antibacterial properties, tea tree oil is too harsh for healing piercings. It can cause skin irritation, allergic reactions, and delay the healing process. Stick to a saline solution recommended by your piercer.
🚫 Bactine: While Bactine may seem appealing as a quick solution, it’s not suitable for piercing aftercare. It contains ingredients like benzalkonium chloride that can be irritating and may impede the healing process.
🚫Dial Soap: Contains harsh chemicals and scents that can be irritating to healing piercings. Dial soap typically has an alkaline pH, which can disrupt the delicate balance of your skin’s natural acidity. This can strip away the natural oils present on your skin. These oils help maintain the skin’s barrier function and promote healing.

Downsizing promotes proper healing and ensures the longevity of your piercing. ⏰📏💍

Remember, your piercer is your partner throughout your piercing journey. They have the expertise and knowledge to guide you towards optimal healing and help you achieve your desired results. 📢 The Importance of Not Starting Most Piercings with a Hoop! 🚫💍 Let’s dive into why professional piercers often avoid using hoops initially for certain piercings. 
Healing and Stability: Piercings need a stable foundation to heal properly. Studs and straight barbells provide better support and reduce the risk of irritation or migration. Hoops, on the other hand, have more movement and can cause unnecessary friction, leading to healing delays or even jewelry embedding.
Irritation and Snagging: Hoops can rotate, twist, and move more freely than studs or barbells. This mobility increases the chances of snagging on clothing, hair, or other objects, which can lead to pain, discomfort, and potential complications.
Swelling Management: Swelling is common in fresh piercings, especially in the early stages of healing. Hoops have a smaller diameter compared to studs or barbells, which can constrict the swollen tissue, causing additional discomfort and hindering the healing process.
Remember, every piercing is unique, and professional piercers assess each individual case to determine the most suitable jewelry options. Once the initial healing phase is complete, and the piercing has stabilized, your piercer may suggest transitioning to a hoop if desired.
Let’s prioritize the health and longevity of our piercings! 🙌💪

A client came in today confused on what is going on with their navel that they got pierced at another local studio and they agreed to let us take a photo to help inform other people that may experience the same issue. This is why it is so important to study which studio you choose, and the piercer that you choose to go too. 
This client was given a prong set gem for their navel piercing that was not suitable for their specific anatomy, this resulted in the gem becoming embedded into their navel, and can potentially leave scarring. 
We offer the wide selection and high quality jewelry options that we do to be able to avoid situations like this. What we would have placed would be something flat to accommodate their anatomy. Sometimes the jewelry we want for fresh piercings, are not suitable right away during healing and it’s important to acknowledge those potential issues that may arise, and offer better solutions for the initial poke. Unfortunately for this client, they were sold whatever jewelry they wanted with no explanation of any potential risks with their choice and was not offered the correct jewelry. 
Please study your shops, piercers, and the piercings you are interested in getting! 
If you are ever confused, worried, or have questions about your piercings feel free to reach out to us! We do not care if you have gotten it pierced by someone else, we are here to help and educate you to happier healthier piercings.
